-- Saks June same-store sales fall 5.6 pct
-- 
-- Thu Jul 12, 2007 8:58am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/07/12/us-saks-sales-idUSBNG4708820070712

 

 (Reuters) - Upscale retailer Saks Inc. SKS.N reported a 5.6 percent fall in June sales at its stores open at least a year and said owned sales fell 3.9 percent to $237.6 million for the month. 

 The company also said it continued to expect low-double digit same-store sales growth for the second quarter. Analysts, on average, had expected the company's June same-store sales to fall 4.8 percent, according to a poll conducted by Reuters. (Reporting by Ramya Dilip in Bangalore)